(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Four divers diced with ragged-tooth sharks at the Two Oceans Aquarium in Cape Town on Tuesday when removing them from an exhibit.WATCHCairo - Egypt has imposed a 15-day ban on sport fishing and offshore swimming near a popular Red Sea destination where a shark attack took place last weekend.Environment Ministry officials Mohamed Salem and Beily Hatab say on Monday the attack was likely caused by the combination of fishing and swimming in the same spot.The shark attack happened off Ain Sokhna, a popular holiday destination 120km east of the Egyptian capital, Cairo. The two officials, who are directly involved in investigating the attack, said the Egyptian man who was bitten by a shark was swimming after bait was thrown nearby.Hotels in the area were instructed to hire watchmen for their beaches.Shark attacks are rare in Egypt.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.